lieve in and calculate the probability of obtaining the observed data under this assumption.</p></li><li><p><strong>Decision-making vs. evaluation:</strong> The current process of hypothesis testing asks researchers to "accept or reject" hypotheses instead of providing a more nuanced evaluation of their likelihood.</p></li><li><p><strong>Long-run frequency misunderstanding:</strong> The p-value refers to the long-run frequency of incorrectly rejecting a true null hypothesis, but researchers are more interested in the correctness of individual hypotheses.</p></li></ol><p>The author notes that while these criticisms have been addressed in the literature, and there have been improvements in statistical education and reporting, these changes are slow. The author also notes that even if statistical inference becomes outdated in future research methodology, the conceptual understanding it provides about cognition and knowledge is still crucial. Thus, there is value in examining and understanding these issues in depth.</p></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-between lg:block"><div class="text-xs flex items-center justify-center gap-1 self-center pt-2 !invisible"><button disabled="" class="dark:text-white disabled:text-gray-300 dark:disabled:text-gray-400"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="h-3 w-3" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"></polyline></svg></button><span class="flex-grow flex-shrink-0">1 / 1</span><button disabled="" class="dark:text-white disabled:text-gray-300 dark:disabled:text-gray-400"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="h-3 w-3" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline></svg></button></div><div class="text-gray-400 flex self-end lg:self-cen